  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency intervention to prevent and to limit the propagation of the Cholera epidemic in South Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Targeted rehabilitation or construction of water and sanitation facilities is included, as coverage of the most vulnerable cases that might be identified, as well as the launching of cholera response and awareness activities in any of the 10 states and quick scale up of the response, in case the outbreak might reach that area. ACF will work on the preparedness activities focusing high risk areas (areas that previously reported some cholera cases in the recent outbreak) and Central and Eastern Equatorial States to prevent the spread of cholera.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The programme is designed in line with the modalities that are being discussed at Cluster level, with special focus on social mobilization, awareness campaign, targeted distributions, surveillance and prompt referral to CTCs.</narrative>
  </description>
